sql:
SELECT year, AVG(quality_score) AS average_quality_score
FROM data_quality
WHERE year = 2000;

SELECT AVG(quality_score) AS average_quality_score
FROM data_quality
WHERE year = 2000;

external_knowledge:
- Europe refers to the region with the name 'Europe' in the regions table; 
- The reporting period of 2006-2010 is defined by the start_year and end_year in the reporting_periods table; 
- Average quality score is the average of the quality_score in the data_quality table; 
- Top 3 emission sources refer to those with the highest average quality scores within each sector, ranked in descending order.

sql:
SELECT source_name, emission_type
FROM emission_sources
WHERE sector_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(source_id) AS source_count
FROM emission_sources
WHERE sector_id = 0;

SELECT sector_name
FROM sectors
ORDER BY sector_name ASC;
